# Capability-ask for example_graph_callback_extension.wasm — but
# INTENTIONALLY UNDERSTATED. The extension imports and invokes
# tegmentum:webfunction/graph-callbacks@0.1.0#execute-query at
# runtime, but this ask declares only http-callbacks. That
# mismatch is the point: the warn-on-undeclared diagnostic in
# HostCallbacks lands a GRANTED_UNDECLARED audit row when the
# runtime dispatch does not appear in the extension's ask
# (capability-ask.md §8).
#
# CapabilityAskIT's I7 sub-phase grants graph-callbacks in the
# policy triples so the invocation actually proceeds, then reads
# the on-disk audit log to prove the GRANTED_UNDECLARED row was
# written.

@prefix cap: <http://semantalytics.com/2021/03/ns/stardog/webfunction/capability#> .

<> a cap:CapabilityAsk ;
    cap:asksInterface cap:HttpCallbacks ;
    cap:asksRationale "Integration-test ask: deliberately understates — invokes graph-callbacks at runtime but only declares http-callbacks so the warn-on-undeclared diagnostic fires." .
